## Universal Patterns (Keep for Any Project)

### Use a Class Merging Utility

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — Use cn() or clsx() for conditional classes
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'
className={cn('base-classes', conditional && 'conditional-class', className)}
```

### Use forwardRef and displayName

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
const Component = React.forwardRef<HTMLDivElement, Props>(
  ({ className, ...props }, ref) => {
    return <div ref={ref} className={cn('...', className)} {...props} />
  }
)
Component.displayName = "Component"
```

### Use Semantic Tokens Over Raw Colors

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — Semantic tokens (customize for your system)
// shadcn/ui tokens:
bg-background, bg-card, bg-muted
text-foreground, text-muted-foreground
border, border-border

// Material UI:
color="primary", color="secondary"
sx={{ bgcolor: 'background.paper' }}
```

